[SN]TITLE[SN]
Arsenal complete the signing of Brazilian defender Andre Santos

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Arsenal have signed Brazilian international left-back Andre Santos from Fenerbahce for £6.2m.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 28-year-old has signed a long-term contract at Emirates Stadium and will wear the number 11 shirt.
Manager Arsene Wenger said: "Santos is a quality player, with the ability to both defend well and get forward."
Santos, who played at the 2011 Copa America, said: "It was one of my dreams to play for a major European football club and I have accomplished this."
After Sunday's 8-2 defeat by Manchester United, Wenger said he was chasing new players before the transfer window closed on 31 August.
Wenger added: "He has experience in the Champions League and for Brazil and has proven he can deliver at the highest level.
"We welcome Santos to the club and look forward to him having a big impact for us."
Last season Santos made 25 league appearances for Fenerbahce, scoring five goals helping them to the Turkish championship.
Full name: Andre Clarindo Dos Santos
Date of birth: 8 March, 1983
Previous clubs: Figueirense, Flamengo (loan), Atletico Miniero (loan), Corinthians, Fenerbahce
International: Brazil - 22 appearances
He said: "I am very happy to be part of this team.
"All the Brazilians who came to this club spoke wonders about it and I am delighted to be part of the Arsenal family."
Fenerbahce announced the transfer to the Istanbul Stock Exchange, quoting 7m euros [£6.2m] for the deal.
Santos played for Brazil as they won the Fifa Confederations Cup in 2009, but he did not make the 23-man squad for the 2010 World Cup Finals. He did return to play in the 2011 Copa America, but missed a penalty as Brazil lost to Paraguay on spot-kicks in the quarter-finals.
He is back in Istanbul to say goodbye to team-mates, coaches and the fans.
Fenerbahce were withdrawn from the Champions League by the Turkish Football Federation following match-fixing allegations and have sold many of their high-profile players.
