He played 21-year-old Kieran Gibbs in that position on the opening day of the season against Newcastle United. but he then injured his hamstring in the Champions League qualifying play-off first leg against Udinese, leaving Bacary Sagna and then Traore to fill in.
Meanwhile, 20-year-old Arsenal forward Gilles Sunu has signed a four-year deal with French first division side Lorient.
The French under-20 international said: "My main aim was to join Lorient so that I can play.
"If I get to play up front I hope to score 10 goals this season."
Arsenal have also sent Costa Rica striker Joel Campbell on loan to French club Lorient until the end of the season.
The 19-year-old striker has only just joined the Gunners from Deportivo Saprissa but the north London club wants him to get first-team experience in France.
